(Henrik groans)
(blades clank)

1:26:16.963 --> 1:26:18.380
(gear clattering)

1:26:18.380 --> 1:26:20.216
(Bjorn grunts)

1:26:20.216 --> 1:26:22.969
(blows thudding)

1:26:25.054 --> 1:26:25.889
(blades whooshing)

1:26:25.889 --> 1:26:27.724
(blades clank)

1:26:27.724 --> 1:26:30.518
(Bjorn groans)

1:26:30.518 --> 1:26:31.394
(Drustan yells)

1:26:31.394 --> 1:26:32.687
(blow thuds)
(Bjorn grunts)

1:26:32.687 --> 1:26:33.813
(blow continues thudding)
- I'm not your-

1:26:33.813 --> 1:26:34.689
(Bjorn groans)

1:26:34.689 --> 1:26:36.648
(blows thudding)
(Bjorn continues groaning)

1:26:36.648 --> 1:26:38.067
(foot thuds)
(Henrik groans)

1:26:38.067 --> 1:26:41.362
(both grunting)
(blows thudding)

1:26:41.362 --> 1:26:42.322
(both groaning)

1:26:42.322 --> 1:26:43.698
(footsteps pattering)

1:26:43.698 --> 1:26:47.368
(Caraphinneth yells in
a mystical language)

1:26:47.368 --> 1:26:50.038
(Drustan yells)

1:26:52.040 --> 1:26:54.125
(Bjorn yells)

1:26:54.125 --> 1:26:56.210
(both grunting)

1:26:56.210 --> 1:26:57.837
(Bjorn screams painfully)

1:26:57.837 --> 1:26:59.964
(headbutt thuds)
(Drustan groans)

1:26:59.964 --> 1:27:02.175
- I'm not your enemy, Ranger!

1:27:02.175 --> 1:27:07.180
(Caraphinneth chants
in a mystical language)

1:27:11.351 --> 1:27:15.188
(Mograh groans)
(skin squelching)

1:27:15.188 --> 1:27:16.773
(continues groaning)

1:27:16.773 --> 1:27:17.815
(pants heavily)

1:27:17.815 --> 1:27:18.650
(sword unsheathes)

1:27:18.650 --> 1:27:20.485
- You'll say anything to stay alive!

1:27:20.485 --> 1:27:21.486
(Drustan yells)

1:27:21.486 --> 1:27:22.320
(sword whooshing)

1:27:22.320 --> 1:27:23.404
(Drustan groans)

1:27:23.404 --> 1:27:24.739
(sword clanks)

1:27:24.739 --> 1:27:25.865
(blow thuds)
(Drustan groans)

1:27:25.865 --> 1:27:28.326
(continues groaning)

1:27:28.326 --> 1:27:30.119
(blow thuds)
(Bjorn groans)

1:27:30.119 --> 1:27:35.124
(Caraphinneth chants
in a mystical language)

1:27:36.960 --> 1:27:38.670
(Bjorn grunts)
(sword clanks)

1:27:38.670 --> 1:27:40.129
(Drustan yells)

1:27:40.129 --> 1:27:41.589
(body thuds)
(Drustan groans)

1:27:41.589 --> 1:27:43.258
(foot thuds)

1:27:43.258 --> 1:27:45.760
(ominous dark music)

1:27:45.760 --> 1:27:46.594
(legs shuffling)

1:27:46.594 --> 1:27:48.429
(sword clanks)

1:27:48.429 --> 1:27:53.434
(Caraphinneth chants
in a mystical language)

1:27:53.893 --> 1:27:54.936
(Drustan groans)

1:27:54.936 --> 1:27:56.020
(sword clanks)

1:27:56.020 --> 1:27:56.853
(Drustan continues groaning)

1:27:56.853 --> 1:27:58.564
- The mighty elven warrior.

1:27:59.648 --> 1:28:00.984
What's the matter, Sharia?

1:28:02.318 --> 1:28:04.612
You're nothing without your blades.

1:28:04.612 --> 1:28:06.114
Here.

1:28:06.114 --> 1:28:08.199
(dagger whooshing)

1:28:08.199 --> 1:28:09.784
Have this one.

1:28:09.784 --> 1:28:10.660
(footsteps pattering)

1:28:10.660 --> 1:28:11.827
(both grunting)

1:28:11.827 --> 1:28:12.662
(feet shuffling)

1:28:12.662 --> 1:28:13.496
(both continue grunting)

1:28:13.496 --> 1:28:14.330
(arrows clatter)
(Drustan groans)

1:28:14.330 --> 1:28:16.040
(Bjorn thuds)

1:28:16.040 --> 1:28:21.045
(Caraphinneth chants
in a mystical language)

1:28:25.008 --> 1:28:28.511
(intense whooshing)

1:28:28.511 --> 1:28:32.014
(Caraphinneth continues chanting)

1:28:32.014 --> 1:28:34.726
(Sharia gagging)

1:28:34.726 --> 1:28:36.184
(Caraphinneth continues chanting)

1:28:36.184 --> 1:28:37.020
(Sharia grunts)
(dagger clanks)

1:28:37.020 --> 1:28:38.103
(Caraphinneth screams)

1:28:38.103 --> 1:28:39.981
(blow thuds)
(Bjorn groans)

1:28:39.981 --> 1:28:41.858
- For my daughter.

1:28:41.858 --> 1:28:42.775
(footsteps pattering)

1:28:42.775 --> 1:28:43.609
(Sharia grunts)
(Drustan groans)

1:28:43.609 --> 1:28:44.485
(body thuds)
(continues groaning)

1:28:44.485 --> 1:28:45.820
(Sharia groans)
Are you mad, She-elf?

1:28:45.820 --> 1:28:46.946
- [Sharia] He's my husband!

1:28:46.946 --> 1:28:50.407
(dramatic instrumental music)

1:28:50.407 --> 1:28:51.242
(Sharia groans)

1:28:51.242 --> 1:28:55.871
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:29:01.044 --> 1:29:02.545
- Forbidden love.

1:29:02.545 --> 1:29:05.465
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:29:05.465 --> 1:29:06.841
(dagger clanks)

1:29:06.841 --> 1:29:11.429
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:29:11.429 --> 1:29:12.347
I understand.

1:29:12.347 --> 1:29:17.018
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:29:24.484 --> 1:29:25.443
(hands thud)

1:29:25.443 --> 1:29:28.821
(intense dramatic music)

1:29:31.449 --> 1:29:32.617
(dagger clanks)

1:29:32.617 --> 1:29:36.871
(intense dramatic music continues)

1:29:38.331 --> 1:29:41.501
(footsteps pattering)

1:29:49.050 --> 1:29:50.300
- Not so fast!

1:29:50.300 --> 1:29:52.678
I've waited a long time for this.

1:29:53.930 --> 1:29:57.517
Now, pastie ranger,
give me your Bloodstone,

1:29:57.517 --> 1:30:02.313
or witness me cut her
little pretty head off.

1:30:02.313 --> 1:30:05.858
- I don't have the Bloodstone.

1:30:05.858 --> 1:30:08.528
You and your kind have raided

1:30:08.528 --> 1:30:12.573
and killed all that were in
my village searching for it.

1:30:14.032 --> 1:30:15.993
No one has it, Mograh.

1:30:15.993 --> 1:30:19.121
- And I beg to differ, Ranger.

1:30:19.121 --> 1:30:20.581
The Lady of the Woods said

1:30:20.581 --> 1:30:24.502
right before I cut her
lights, you'd have it.

1:30:24.502 --> 1:30:27.130
And if I found you, I'd get it.

1:30:27.130 --> 1:30:28.840
I'd live forever.

1:30:28.840 --> 1:30:31.467
(dramatic instrumental music)

1:30:31.467 --> 1:30:33.010
(intense whooshing)

1:30:33.010 --> 1:30:35.304
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:30:35.304 --> 1:30:36.973
(intense whooshing)

1:30:36.973 --> 1:30:38.391
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:30:38.391 --> 1:30:40.643
(intense whooshing)

1:30:40.643 --> 1:30:41.853
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:30:41.853 --> 1:30:43.228
(intense whooshing)

1:30:43.228 --> 1:30:46.773
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:30:46.773 --> 1:30:48.943
(intense whooshing)

1:30:48.943 --> 1:30:53.614
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:31:03.791 --> 1:31:04.834
(intense whooshing)
The thing about

1:31:04.834 --> 1:31:08.254
the Lady of the Woods is, she never lies.

1:31:09.297 --> 1:31:12.717
(intense dramatic music)

1:31:17.180 --> 1:31:19.223
(stuffed animal rustles)

1:31:19.223 --> 1:31:23.478
(intense dramatic music continues)

1:31:47.710 --> 1:31:48.669
(necklace thuds)

1:31:48.669 --> 1:31:52.924
(intense dramatic music continues)

1:32:02.308 --> 1:32:04.727
Oi, Caraphinneth, finish him.

1:32:08.606 --> 1:32:09.440
(Caraphinneth grunts)

1:32:09.440 --> 1:32:11.776
(arrows clatter)
(air whooshing)

1:32:11.776 --> 1:32:12.610
(Drustan groans)

1:32:12.610 --> 1:32:13.903
(skin squelching)
(Caraphinneth grunts)

1:32:13.903 --> 1:32:16.697
(whimpers softly)

1:32:24.080 --> 1:32:27.416
(Mograh thuds)

1:32:27.416 --> 1:32:30.962
(skin squelching)
(Caraphinneth grunts)

1:32:30.962 --> 1:32:32.838
(Drustan grunts)
(Caraphinneth groans)

1:32:32.838 --> 1:32:34.048
(body thuds)

1:32:34.048 --> 1:32:36.717
(dramatic instrumental music)

1:32:36.717 --> 1:32:37.885
(sword clanks)

1:32:37.885 --> 1:32:38.886
(leaves rustling)

1:32:38.886 --> 1:32:42.139
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:32:42.139 --> 1:32:43.182
(Henrik pants heavily)

1:32:43.182 --> 1:32:44.225
(bow creaks)

1:32:44.225 --> 1:32:46.727
(arrow whooshing)
(Henrik groans)

1:32:46.727 --> 1:32:48.187
(arrow whooshing)

1:32:48.187 --> 1:32:51.857
(Henrik continues groaning)

1:32:53.859 --> 1:32:54.693
(bow creaks)

1:32:54.693 --> 1:32:56.654
(Henrik groans loudly)
- Wait!

1:32:56.654 --> 1:32:58.906
(continues groaning)

1:32:58.906 --> 1:33:00.532
He is my brother.

1:33:00.532 --> 1:33:02.243
(Henrik breathes heavily)

1:33:02.243 --> 1:33:07.248
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:33:07.623 --> 1:33:08.541
(sword clanks)

1:33:08.541 --> 1:33:13.212
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:33:18.675 --> 1:33:19.885
(Mograh thuds)

1:33:19.885 --> 1:33:21.219
(whimsical tones)

1:33:21.219 --> 1:33:25.891
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:33:29.061 --> 1:33:31.063
- So you'll kill me then?

1:33:31.063 --> 1:33:33.107
Your own brother?

1:33:33.107 --> 1:33:34.817
You have no loyalty, Bjorn.

1:33:36.235 --> 1:33:37.695
You will die!

1:33:37.695 --> 1:33:39.155
She will betray you!

1:33:40.072 --> 1:33:42.907
You know not what you choose.

1:33:42.907 --> 1:33:44.493
- It didn't have to be this way.

1:33:45.745 --> 1:33:48.289
- Your stupid and weak!

1:33:48.289 --> 1:33:50.291
Curses be upon you, Bjorn!

1:33:51.416 --> 1:33:52.877
(Henrik groans)
(skin squelching)

1:33:52.877 --> 1:33:56.297
(gurgles loudly)

1:33:56.297 --> 1:33:58.633
(pants heavily)

1:33:58.633 --> 1:34:03.304
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:34:09.226 --> 1:34:11.312
- Goodbye, brother.

1:34:11.312 --> 1:34:13.606
May you fair better in the afterlife

1:34:13.606 --> 1:34:15.650
than you did in this one.

1:34:15.650 --> 1:34:18.402
(ominous dramatic music)
(sword clanks)

1:34:18.402 --> 1:34:21.781
(ominous dramatic music continues)

1:34:21.781 --> 1:34:22.615
- [Reina] Daddy!

1:34:24.157 --> 1:34:27.202
(dark ominous music)

1:34:29.330 --> 1:34:33.166
(dramatic instrumental music)

1:34:44.594 --> 1:34:45.680
- Reina, my child.

1:34:49.892 --> 1:34:53.646
You are so strong and brave.

1:34:56.273 --> 1:34:58.025
You are my everything.

1:34:58.025 --> 1:35:02.697
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:35:06.617 --> 1:35:09.829
Never forget how special you are.

1:35:15.501 --> 1:35:18.796
(smooching softly)

1:35:18.796 --> 1:35:23.050
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:35:23.050 --> 1:35:23.884
(water rushing)

1:35:23.884 --> 1:35:28.556
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:35:50.244 --> 1:35:53.289
Reina, love, this is our new home now.

1:35:55.249 --> 1:35:57.710
This is where you stay
when I fight for the king.

1:36:01.380 --> 1:36:02.548
You're with family now.

1:36:03.924 --> 1:36:08.596
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:36:13.601 --> 1:36:14.559
- Hi, Reina.

1:36:14.559 --> 1:36:15.561
I'm Evaline.

1:36:15.561 --> 1:36:17.146
Would you like to come play?

1:36:17.146 --> 1:36:21.776
(dramatic instrumental music continues)

1:36:30.701 --> 1:36:32.327
- Thank you.

1:36:32.327 --> 1:36:34.371
- We are not your enemy, Ranger.

1:36:35.331 --> 1:36:36.165
- It would seem,

1:36:36.165 --> 1:36:38.041
given the rare circumstances
of the situation,

1:36:38.041 --> 1:36:40.419
which was the only option that could work.

1:36:40.419 --> 1:36:42.129
I am the last surviving Outlander.

1:36:43.005 --> 1:36:44.380
- Only we know where the hidden camp is

1:36:44.380 --> 1:36:47.175
that the dark shroud protects.

1:36:47.175 --> 1:36:49.844
- [Drustan] I suppose it's the
safest possible place then.

1:36:49.844 --> 1:36:50.846
- For them both.

1:36:53.766 --> 1:36:54.975
- I couldn't agree more.

1:36:56.309 --> 1:36:59.730
(intense dramatic music)

1:37:33.472 --> 1:37:34.306
- Ranger!

1:37:36.934 --> 1:37:41.188
(intense dramatic music continues)

1:37:58.873 --> 1:38:00.249
- [Drustan] It's finally over.

1:38:00.249 --> 1:38:01.083
(bag rustles)

1:38:01.083 --> 1:38:02.835
The long awaited rest.

1:38:04.128 --> 1:38:08.549
I feel free to act, free to serve.

1:38:09.967 --> 1:38:14.471
My sweet Reina safe and
sound with newfound friends

1:38:14.471 --> 1:38:15.764
who have become family.

1:38:17.224 --> 1:38:20.269
Curious how the shedding
of blood does that.

1:38:20.269 --> 1:38:22.478
How it renders preconceived ideas

1:38:22.478 --> 1:38:27.151
of what we once thought were
just and true irrelevant.

1:38:28.277 --> 1:38:29.945
But how did I become this,

1:38:31.530 --> 1:38:32.656
a creature of light?

1:38:33.699 --> 1:38:37.244
Was I forged in the furnace
of war like so many of us?

1:38:38.829 --> 1:38:39.914
I think not.

1:38:40.831 --> 1:38:42.082
I was saved,

1:38:43.041 --> 1:38:45.960
saved by a guardian
who saw better than me.

1:38:47.630 --> 1:38:50.966
Wrapped by sorrow from the
death of the Ancient One,

1:38:50.966 --> 1:38:52.968
I grew powerless to resist the urge

1:38:52.968 --> 1:38:56.013
to track down the thieving
bandits who stole his life.

1:38:56.889 --> 1:38:59.141
A promise I had made knowing full well

1:38:59.141 --> 1:39:00.809
I hadn't the strength to fulfill.

1:39:02.019 --> 1:39:03.145
The flesh is weak,

1:39:03.145 --> 1:39:05.689
and I succumb to the poison of vengeance.

1:39:06.898 --> 1:39:09.276
After many days of tracking,

1:39:09.276 --> 1:39:11.403
I finally took hold of their scent.

1:39:12.737 --> 1:39:14.031
What would happen next

1:39:14.031 --> 1:39:17.117
could only be explained as fate incarnate.

1:39:17.117 --> 1:39:20.537
(ominous dramatic music)

1:39:24.375 --> 1:39:26.335
- For a thievin' bandit like yourself,

1:39:26.335 --> 1:39:28.587
I didn't think you had it in ya.

1:39:28.587 --> 1:39:30.047
- [Drustan] Only two bandits.

1:39:30.047 --> 1:39:31.799
Where's the third?

1:39:31.799 --> 1:39:35.803
No matter, I could just
end them with arrows,

1:39:35.803 --> 1:39:38.389
but they need to be punished.

1:39:38.389 --> 1:39:39.306
- [Boss Bandit] They were ugly,

1:39:39.306 --> 1:39:41.016
(laughs) maybe that was why?

1:39:42.017 --> 1:39:43.978
- [Drustan] They don't
deserve a quick end.

1:39:43.978 --> 1:39:44.853
(fruit thuds)

1:39:44.853 --> 1:39:46.522
(Drustan groans)
(blow thuds)

1:39:46.522 --> 1:39:47.356
(liquid sloshing)

1:39:47.356 --> 1:39:48.523
(blows continue thudding)

1:39:48.523 --> 1:39:49.566
(Boss Bandit groans)

1:39:49.566 --> 1:39:50.776
(blows continue thudding)

1:39:50.776 --> 1:39:52.945
- Oh, you're mad (laughs).

1:39:52.945 --> 1:39:54.196
(blow thuds)
(arrow clatters)

1:39:54.196 --> 1:39:55.072
(blows continue thudding)

1:39:55.072 --> 1:39:56.240
(sword clanks)

1:39:56.240 --> 1:39:58.659
(air whooshing)
(skin squelching)

1:39:58.659 --> 1:40:00.327
You and your poison.

1:40:01.996 --> 1:40:03.580
(Drustan groans painfully)

1:40:03.580 --> 1:40:05.708
(Boss Bandit laughs)

1:40:05.708 --> 1:40:09.460
(Drustan continues groaning)

1:40:16.260 --> 1:40:18.053
What you're experiencing right now

1:40:18.053 --> 1:40:21.139
are the effects of a
decade long obsession.

1:40:21.139 --> 1:40:22.975
Kreiger here loves his poison.

1:40:22.975 --> 1:40:25.144
Now, I know Kreiger would love to

1:40:25.144 --> 1:40:27.521
explain the details of his concoction,

1:40:27.521 --> 1:40:30.357
but, well, years of
dedication to his craft

1:40:30.357 --> 1:40:31.900
have shriveled his tongue.

1:40:31.900 --> 1:40:33.193
Oh, don't worry,
(Drustan groans painfully)

1:40:33.193 --> 1:40:35.237
his poison won't kill ya.

1:40:35.237 --> 1:40:36.864
It'll just
(Drustan groans)

1:40:36.864 --> 1:40:40.784
incapacitate ya long
enough for us to kill.

1:40:42.036 --> 1:40:44.079
(Drustan continues groaning)

1:40:44.079 --> 1:40:46.790
(ax unsheathing)

1:40:46.790 --> 1:40:51.170
(Drustan continues groaning)

1:40:51.170 --> 1:40:52.796
(footsteps pattering)

1:40:52.796 --> 1:40:53.922
(blow thuds)
(arrows clatter)

1:40:53.922 --> 1:40:56.675
(both grunting)

1:40:56.675 --> 1:40:57.550
(sword clanks)

1:40:57.550 --> 1:40:58.594
(male groans)
(metal clangs)

1:40:58.594 --> 1:41:01.180
(metal clanks)

1:41:06.059 --> 1:41:09.563
(Drustan grunts softly)

1:41:09.563 --> 1:41:12.398
(apple crunching)

1:41:14.443 --> 1:41:17.862
- (sighs) What happened?

1:41:19.531 --> 1:41:21.742
- You were caught in a moment of weakness.

1:41:22.659 --> 1:41:23.535
You were spared.

1:41:26.496 --> 1:41:27.331
- Thank you.

1:41:27.331 --> 1:41:29.666
- But how eager you were
to forsake your oath.

1:41:31.293 --> 1:41:32.127
- Who are you?

1:41:32.127 --> 1:41:33.879
How do you know of my oath?

1:41:33.879 --> 1:41:36.298
- I am the watcher of these woods,

1:41:36.298 --> 1:41:39.050
and I know that you swore an
oath to your ancient ancestor

1:41:39.050 --> 1:41:42.054
that you would not seek
vengeance upon his killers.

1:41:42.054 --> 1:41:45.307
As I said, you were weak,

1:41:45.307 --> 1:41:46.850
and now I have spared you.

1:41:50.353 --> 1:41:51.939
- [Drustan] Spared me from what?

1:41:53.315 --> 1:41:54.775
- An awful fate, my friend,

1:41:56.485 --> 1:41:59.071
one that would consume your every thought,

1:41:59.071 --> 1:42:01.740
one that would lead you straight
to the forces of darkness.

1:42:01.740 --> 1:42:03.242
- And how do you know of this?

1:42:04.326 --> 1:42:08.330
- I was where you were once
after the death, Kiera.

1:42:13.001 --> 1:42:14.210
I was a lost soul.

1:42:15.587 --> 1:42:16.672
The Ancient One helped me

1:42:16.672 --> 1:42:19.133
fight against the darkness that crept in.

1:42:20.425 --> 1:42:21.760
I became a force for light.

1:42:23.637 --> 1:42:26.348
After I pledged myself to
protect the Borderlands,

1:42:27.683 --> 1:42:30.269
I fought the forces of
darkness for quite some time.

1:42:31.895 --> 1:42:34.731
And I remembered the
Ancient One telling me

1:42:35.607 --> 1:42:37.860
of a lost love and family he once had.

1:42:39.903 --> 1:42:41.572
I returned to these part.

1:42:43.448 --> 1:42:45.617
I've watched you train
for quite some time.

1:42:47.119 --> 1:42:51.039
I saw your potential
in skill and the heart.

1:42:52.541 --> 1:42:53.375
(fire whooshing)

1:42:53.375 --> 1:42:55.335
I witnessed his passing,

1:42:57.171 --> 1:43:01.758
and I witnessed your
oath sealed by his blood.

1:43:04.011 --> 1:43:06.680
(intense whooshing)

1:43:06.680 --> 1:43:10.559
- It would seem I owe
you a life debt, Ranger.

1:43:10.559 --> 1:43:11.476
- On the contrary.

1:43:13.228 --> 1:43:15.689
It is he who owes you a life debt.

1:43:20.235 --> 1:43:22.779
This here is the last remaining bandit.

1:43:24.198 --> 1:43:26.532
He claims he was forced
to kill the Ancient One,

1:43:26.532 --> 1:43:28.368
that he had no choice in the matter.

1:43:29.912 --> 1:43:32.496
I leave judgment to you, Drustan.

1:43:34.208 --> 1:43:35.666
As rangers in the Borderlands,

1:43:35.666 --> 1:43:37.920
we are the blade of the king.

1:43:37.920 --> 1:43:41.005
We are judge, jury and executioner.

1:43:42.257 --> 1:43:44.343
So what will it be, brother?

1:43:46.511 --> 1:43:48.388
Will it be justice or mercy?

1:43:56.021 --> 1:43:58.773
(birds chirping)

1:44:00.108 --> 1:44:03.946
(dramatic instrumental music)

1:44:44.820 --> 1:44:47.614
(whimsical tones)

1:44:49.657 --> 1:44:52.744
(dark ominous music)

1:45:22.523 --> 1:45:24.609
(child chants indistinctly)

1:45:24.609 --> 1:45:28.572
(triumphant instrumental music)

1:46:01.897 --> 1:46:05.192
(gentle ethereal music)
